05648nam a22007935i 9781552385357DE-B159720240306010644.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20122011xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97815523853577 a10.1515/97815523853572doi  a(DE-B1597)663832  a(OCoLC)1412008711  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 4aN6549.C35C69 2011 7aART0150402bisacsh04a741.609200aCover and Uncover :bEric Cameron /ced. by Ann Davis. 1aCalgary, Alberta : bUniversity of Calgary Press, c[2012] 4cÂ©2011  a1 online resource (190 p.) :b56 black & white illustrations, bibliography, index  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aArt in Profile: Canadian Art and Architecture ;v1000tFront Matter -- tTable of Contents -- tAcknowledgments -- tList of Illustrations -- tTo Uncover: An Introduction -- tEric Cameron: Author! Author! -- tAristotle and Material Mysticism: Process Paintings and Beyond -- tThe "Imperfect" Artist: Eric Cameron's Video Work -- tSome Philosophical Implications of Eric Cameron's "Routine Extremism" -- tEric Cameron: Bibliography -- tNotes on Contributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aEric Cameron is a major contemporary Canadian artist. Born in 1935 in Leicester, England, he arrived in Canada in the 1970s and has taught at the University of Guelph, the Nova Scotia College of Art and Design, and at the University of Calgary. Over the years Cameron has also continued to work in his primary medium, painting, but moved from traditional figuration to a highly conceptual practice with both his process paintings and his "thick" paintings. He has also expanded into video and has written a great deal about his work. His inspired teaching and unusual art have been recognized with major awards, including the Victor Lynch-Staunton Award (1993), the Gershorn Iskowitz Prize (1994), and the Governor General's Award (2004). Despite Cameron's prominence, much of the writing about him to date, primarily essays in exhibition catalogues, is by the artist himself. Cover and Uncover thus makes a major contribution to the field as it explores in depth Eric Cameron's art and philosophy. The book is composed of four essays, each covering a different aspect of Cameron's art, starting with Peggy Gale's analysis of his writing, then turning to Ann Davis's consideration of his process paintings and his philosophy, moving to Diana Nemiroff's review of his videos, and concluding with Thierry de Duve's observations on his Thick Paintings and his blind rejection of chance. The essays, though written independently, resonate with each other so that the reader comes away with a full picture of a complex artist, his life, his thought, his art production, and how these elements inform each other and have evolved through time. The expert commentary here, richly illustrated with Cameron's works in multiple media, provides a vital and long overdue critical lens through which to view this important artist. With Contributions By: Ann Davis Thierry de Duve Peggy Gale Diana Nemiroff  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArtists -- Canada -- Biography. 0aCameron, Eric, -- 1935- -- Criticism and interpretation. 0aCameron, Eric, -- 1935-. 0aPainters -- Canada -- Biography. 7aART / Canadian.2bisacsh  aaward winning artist calgary.  acalgary artist book.  acalgary artist.  aconceptual art practice.  aconceptual art.  aeric cameron artist.  aeric cameron book.  aeric cameron calgary.  amajor artist calgary.  amodern calgary artist.  amodern canadian artists.  aphilosophy of art.  aphilosophy of conceptual art.  atraditional figuration.  avideo art.1 aDavis, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Ann, 